.TH ETOPO2SHAPE 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
etopo2shape \- build elevation contour polygons from ETOPO2 data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B etopo2shape
.RI [ options ]
.I shapename
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B etopo2shape
reads the global ETOPO2 topography raster (2\(hyminute resolution),
contours the heights at the requested levels and writes the resulting
polygons as an ESRI shapefile. The path to the ETOPO2 binary is read
from the
.B rasters::etopo2
setting in the SmartMet configuration. Compressed
.RB ( .gz ", " .bz2 )
inputs are decompressed transparently.
.PP
Each output polygon carries an integer
.B HEIGHT
attribute equal to the contour level it was generated from. Negative
values produce contours of the lower\(hybound type; the default level
set is suitable for Scandinavia.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print help.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode.
.TP
.BI \-b " x1,y1,x2,y2"
Bounding box (longitude/latitude) to extract. Default is roughly
Scandinavia
.RI ( 6,51,49,71 ).
.TP
.BI \-l " h1,h2,..."
Comma\(hyseparated list of heights, in metres, at which to contour.
Default is
.IR 100,200,300,500,700,1000 .
.SH EXAMPLES
Default Scandinavian contours:
.PP
.RS 4
etopo2shape topo
.RE
.PP
Custom area and levels:
.PP
.RS 4
etopo2shape \-b \-25,35,45,72 \-l 50,200,500,1000,2000 europe_topo
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lights2shape (1),
.BR gshhs2shape (1),
.BR shape2ps (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
